  "text": "The main difference between fundamental diagrams of (3.2), see Figure 5 , right, and that of (1.4) is that (3.2) requires the two phases to be disconnected: there is a gap between the free and the congested phase. This restriction is necessary for the well posedness of the Riemann problem for (3.2) and can be hardly justified on the basis of experimental data. More recently, the global well-posedness of the model (3.2) was proved in [CITATION_1] .",
